<paragraph id="6DC5D6A27F06FACA7B81FAD23BB5EF4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">[Germany] an einer Sandsteinmauer in den Weinbergen bei Neuenheim, Febr. 1863, W. von Zwackh (M-0023494!, syntype?).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF398890E108A5EF44F97FE9B8683374" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="B02E7F7D45A5E5583B1FCEA0FC1F83A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E65264AAB8B0DFCF3ED5FECE53A90C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus pale grey, rimose to areolate, areoles 0.3-0.7 mm. Perithecia 0.22-0.26 mm, immersed in thallus. Involucrellum absent. Exciple wall pale. Periphysoids ca. 50-80 
<normalizedToken id="75DBC69049D80E7649135D3540BDA67B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 mm, branching. Ascospores 0-septate (only few seen), 20-28 
<normalizedToken id="23C67F126C5FBBA9754D8034D717842F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
13-14 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E8B1C30D166E188E9C66CD4A7FD43022" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C70A9F2727D5E3D12567C2AE6388BEFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="701289B53AC93188481380D94580EDEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<bibRefCitation id="215B545354E618F79A4264A459B124F7" author="Krzewicka, B" journalOrPublisher="Polish Botanical Studies" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 143" refId="B20" refString="Krzewicka, B, 2012. A revision of Verrucaria s. l. (Verrucariaceae) in Poland. Polish Botanical Studies 27: 1 - 143" title="A revision of Verrucaria s. l. (Verrucariaceae) in Poland." volume="27" year="2012">Krzewicka (2012)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="C79DB57BA81FB2D32891B90239BF5400" genus="V." lsidName="V. carnea" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="carnea">
<emphasis id="380A3D4331D34F39C7A32F0BF42869DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. carnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a pigment-deficient mutant of 
<taxonomicName id="F867F8F321CAEC14DA2F0B3AE5BD76EF" genus="V." lsidName="V. hochstetteri" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="hochstetteri">
<emphasis id="3DC6EFDE3EE7ED5B89217328D5B69F7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. hochstetteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Gilbert (1996) as an albino form of 
<taxonomicName id="D3312D1F6C2006D4FB7FD695D4851F44" genus="V." lsidName="V. macrostoma" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="macrostoma">
<emphasis id="BFD2333C51D4B63EEAA7658F64637DC6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. macrostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dufour ex DC. However, it differs in several morphological characters from these species. 
<bibRefCitation id="63E3F1EBA25EB5581AD5CC12D037AC53" DOI="https://doi.org/10.13158/099.031.0117" author="Oihenart, M" journalOrPublisher="Herzogia" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="209 - 218" refId="B27" refString="Oihenart, M, Clerc, P, Breuss, O, 2018. New and interesting species of the lichen genus Verrucaria (Verrucariaceae, Ascomycota) for Switzerland and France. Herzogia 31 (1): 209 - 218, DOI: https://doi.org/10.13158/099.031.0117" title="New and interesting species of the lichen genus Verrucaria (Verrucariaceae, Ascomycota) for Switzerland and France." url="https://doi.org/10.13158/099.031.0117" volume="31" year="2018">
<normalizedToken id="5CEE0513CC583C3D82E6DF0614E058E9" originalValue="Oïhénart">Oihenart</normalizedToken>
et al. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted 
<taxonomicName id="D1D5E760F03E6B985EF73E96EEA408ED" genus="V." lsidName="V. carnea" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="carnea">
<emphasis id="182AF35FB53721275679857DC8F751E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. carnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
